The verdict is not final, the appeal of the convicted person is to be heard by the court in December.
Tymoshenko describes the verdict as the political revenge of the regime, suspicion of court bias has provoked trial in the West.
The proposal to delete section 365 from the Criminal Code, on the basis of which the ex-prime minister was convicted, was supported by 147 deputies in the vote.
