Obese child&#39;s diet: no breakfast and cold cuts for dinner
More than a third of children aged 9 to 13 have overweight problems, with 9 percent of schoolchildren being overweight and 5 percent being obese.
Obese children usually come from families with unhealthy lifestyles, as the current survey has shown.
It shows once again how important the environment in which he grows up and the patterns with which he is surrounded is important for the healthy development of man.
For example, sausages appear on the tables of obese children up to half as often as in families of children with normal weight.
More than 19 percent of obese people had fried fries for dinner the day before the research associated with the awareness event called Obesity.
It is also not customary in families of fat people to play sports, which is true of most families of today&#39;s schoolchildren - only 15 percent of children said that their parents find time for active movement at least once a week.
Survey among 900 children
The survey took place at the end of last school year and was attended by almost 900 children from primary schools from all over the Czech Republic.
It was the second year of the Obesity is No Coincidence event, which is supported by Všeobecná zdravotní pojišťovna and Unilever.
So far, more than 12,000 schoolchildren from 4th to 8th grades have joined the project.
Proper nutrition and enough exercise in the family is one of the determining factors, which causes a dramatically increasing number of overweight or even obese children.
&quot;Only half of the respondents, for example, said that they eat five times a day in the breakfast-snack-lunch-snack-dinner regime, which is one of the basic prerequisites for proper nutrition,&quot; said one of the results of the survey.
Without breakfast and cold cuts in the evening
Experts point out that relative details, such as regular family breakfasts, are also important for healthy development.
In the Czech Republic, at the same time, only 23 percent of schoolchildren have breakfast.
In most families, everyone has breakfast alone.
And the worst thing was finding that in a tenth of households they don&#39;t eat breakfast at all.
Breakfast is the basis of a proper daily diet.
The questionnaire showed that unhealthy fries are much more often consumed in families of obese children.
Almost everyone - regardless of weight - drinks sweet lemonade every day (70 percent).
Although more than 40 percent of the children surveyed play sports regularly, the result for their parents was less than half - 15 percent.
Build your menu
Another part of the survey allowed selected children (204 boys and 172 girls from 13 schools) to compile their own diet from the options offered according to their own taste and opinion.
&quot;The dietary preferences of Czech children aged 12 to 15 are far from ideal in terms of healthy nutrition.&quot;
Among their favorite dishes are a lot of floury, meat and sweet dishes.
&quot;The great popularity of sweet lemonades is particularly alarming,&quot; the survey said in the final report.
For lunch as a main course, pasta won just over poultry.
However, the children practically did not want legumes at all, and the popularity of fish and lunch vegetable dishes is also low.
Leaning towards health
At the same time, the survey showed that children are willing to adjust their eating habits if they are given the right information.
&quot;In the control group of survey participants who filled out the questionnaire after the obesity lecture, there is no coincidence in many cases, there was a significant shift in preferences towards the principles of healthy nutrition,&quot; the project said.
This was striking, for example, with sweet lemonades, where more children would start to prefer ordinary water.
Children were also much more likely to tick poultry and fish as the main meal of the day in the questionnaire and would reduce sweet foods and dumplings.
The stylist must also be a good psychologist, say the pros
In the introductory article on how stylists learn, I complained so much that there was already a lot in the introductory class.
I had no idea what would follow.
Lectures by three professionals from the field, dressing problematic characters and a seminar on how it goes on the spot.
And it will get worse.
The closer to the final exam, the more information and practical tasks await us.
And even though the course takes place every Saturday and Sunday, it is really &quot;trampled&quot;.
This time, director Alenka and I discussed (there is not a single boy in the course) how to dress a woman who does not have a perfectly symmetrical figure.
And the vast majority of them are.
Some have a short neck, some have a boyish figure without proper curves and some are overweight.
The stylist must know how to optically soften wide shoulders, lengthen the neck or deliver the necessary curves.
We got tips on how to emphasize the figure nicely with a woman like Jennifer Lopez, ie bigger breasts and hips and a narrow waist, and at the same time not dress the woman too defiantly.
For example, if the difference between the waist and the hips is such that the skirt or trousers do not really fit, then it pays to have at least one such piece tailored.
You will definitely not regret it, because perfectly fitting clothes are priceless.
You will feel much better in a tailor-made skirt than in one that is constantly shifting, rolling up, standing out at the waist and the like.
The boy character, on the other hand, can afford to wear clothes with ruffles, applications, embroidery or gathering.
Of course, there is a lot of such information and character types, so I&#39;m glad I have a whole week to sort all the information in my head.
And I&#39;m still afraid that, given the homework assignment, it&#39;s up to that.
Each of the course participants was assigned an celebrity to come up with two outfits: day and evening.
We have to take into account the current look, fashion style of the personality and type of figure.
I&#39;m going to &quot;dress&quot; Miranda Kerr, maybe you know her from Victoria&#39;s Secret campaigns.
In my mind, I&#39;m cheering, definitely better for me personally than Britney Spears, Christina Aguilera, who has recently gained perhaps a hundred kilos (please take exaggeration), or the young Selena Gomez.
We have to cut out the clothes from magazines or search the Internet and print them out and then process them graphically.
Moodboard, as the whole result is called, then expresses our personal style and relationship to the graphic design.
It is also important to think about the graphic side of styling.
The stylist not only dresses physically, but also creates, for example, so-called product pages in magazines (for specific assignments, such as trendy handbags, coats, etc.).
Stylist and designer Mario Kameník told us about it.
But not until Sunday.
The stylist must have a general overview
Saturday&#39;s lecture, full of information about the types of characters, was enriched by three guests from the field.
Stylist Honza Pokorný, fashion designer Jakub Polanka and fashion photographer Ben Renč.
Jakub reminded us that fashion is an illusion and a stylist should be able to use it.
And a skilled stylist can work with one piece of clothing in different ways.
Variability is key in this case.
For example, such a trench coat (or, if you want originally a trench coat) can be worn classically over jeans and a T-shirt as a coat, but you can also wear it on the bare body, put on pumps and take pictures as a dress.
Or just roll up your sleeves or collar and the whole look looks different.
&quot;Play with it,&quot; he stressed.
But what I appreciated most was the following advice: &quot;You need to know the rules perfectly to work.&quot;
&quot;Then you can start breaking them,&quot; Jakub said.
Finally, it is clear to me why we are crushing all the lessons, what to combine with what, why, why, when we often see something else in fashion magazines.
Not to mention the shows.
Thanks to photographer Ben, I know that the stylist must have many more clothing variants ready than there are photos to be photographed.
So for a fashion story that will have ten pages (that is, ten outfits), I have to be prepared to &quot;set up&quot; at least fifteen.
And also that in the photo the clothes look and work in combination with other pieces sometimes completely differently than in reality.
So we have to take this into account when creating an outfit.
Honza Pokorný confirmed to us that image and style sometimes do up to half the success.
Just look at Madonna, who is not exactly a miracle singer, but her image and marketing have made her a world star.
In the Czech Republic, the approach to using the services of stylists is still rather cold.
Even familiar faces sometimes consider it useless (it is enough that I can do something, the way I look at it is secondary).
And if someone has a styling created by us, then we have to reckon with the fact that they most likely dictate a completely different (smaller) size to us than they really have.
Then all that remains is to googgle and see if the boulevard has written that the celebrity has gained weight / weight and the like.
On Sunday, both Honza and Mario told us that it was not enough for a stylist to orient himself in fashion and be able to put together an outfit.
In his work, he mainly communicates with the people he dresses, so it is important to be a good psychologist.
To be able to guess people, not to encourage oneself, to stand up for one&#39;s opinion.
&quot;When a manager orders you to sort her wardrobe and add nice pieces, you can&#39;t throw her out of the closet and say, for God&#39;s sake, that&#39;s horrible.&quot;
&quot;Find at least a few things to praise and recommend what to wear,&quot; says Mario.
He also specifically showed us what all the so-called &quot;placovka&quot; must contain, or a bag for a place.
It&#39;s the one you fasten around your waist and you have all the necessary properties with you.
In addition to clear things, such as scissors, a hair roller or safety pins, there is also a nylon thread (with it, the stylist helps with the shooting of products such as handbags or hats), special clips to fasten the back of clothing, if larger (pin or other staples are not allowed, they would damage the garment) or the sewing kit.
In order not only to listen, but also to try something in practice, we learned how to glue the shoes properly.
Even when shooting in a studio where the surface is flat, the sole could be damaged, let alone outdoors.
And so we glued and glued.
We must not even use the scissors to touch the shoes so that they are not accidentally damaged.
So you really need skill.
Mario pleased me when he praised my creation without reservation.
The mentioned skill is really not my friend.
This is just a tiny fraction of what we heard about the second weekend of the course.
It&#39;s becoming increasingly clear to me that a professional-style styling isn&#39;t really a walk in the rose garden, no matter who wants what.
In Need for Speed: The Run, they race across America.
Review
Originally a carefree ride, it turns into a routine morning trip to the shift due to a series of completely unnecessary sloppy mistakes.
The ambitions have been largely fulfilled, but this is not valid when no one clearly wanted to do anything extra.
The new episode, subtitled The Run, raised high expectations before its release.
He promised to move the age-old racing series Need for Speed a bit in a new direction again, and from the playable demonstrations he seemed like a game that wouldn&#39;t have to be just in numbers in the action racing genre.
We were also curious how the inserted passages would turn out, in which the main character gets out of the car and runs his own way.
However, as is customary with the NFS series, many are a little different than we expected.
These are potentially decent arcade races, but the whole thing pulls down a few unnecessary mistakes that have been appearing in the series for more or less several years.
So it&#39;s not really a mistake, but rather a manifestation of some incomprehensible laziness of the developers.
The adventure starts very well.
You are introduced to a story whose main character Jack has certain personal problems and as a solution is to participate in an illegal race across America.
You will get behind the wheel on the west coast of San Francisco and your task is to arrive in New York first.
The idea carries several interesting elements.
The route is divided into ten stages, and then into more than fifty races.
It follows that each race is run on a different track and the stages are set in different, sufficiently different and interesting environments.
One does not feel even for a moment that the game would always offer the same thing.
In addition, some of the environments are very nice to look at, although the technical level of the graphics corresponds to the previous parts of the series.
So it&#39;s nothing world-breaking.
But driving across the desert, autumn landscape or high in the snowy mountains is very visually pleasing.
In addition, the races are diversified from time to time with some atypical element.
In the desert, for example, you get caught up in a sandstorm, which greatly reduces visibility.
In the mountains, on the other hand, you have to be careful not to be overwhelmed by an avalanche.
In addition, the individual races are deployed quite well in a row.
There are only a few types, but that&#39;s enough.
For a while you try to overtake the required number of opponents (basically a classic race), then you catch up again (classic duel with a stopwatch) and then a duel with a single opponent awaits you.
From time to time, the police will get involved, making your whole effort even more uncomfortable.
A novelty are the passages outside the car.
It&#39;s more just an interactive animation, where Jack usually runs away from someone and you have to help him by pressing the right buttons at the right moments.
Nothing complicated.
But it is surprising that there are far fewer of these passages in the game than you would expect (specifically, perhaps even just three).
As a result, however, it is to the benefit of the matter, because this element does not have a chance to become annoying, and in the context of the above, it is one of the elements that diversify the game.
The ride model follows in the footsteps of previous parts.
This means that it is definitely not anything nowadays, but it cannot be said that it is a negative.
If you are looking for a realistic simulation, you will have to look elsewhere.
But the local driving model still suits the more action-packed racing quite well, even though we could find a better one in the competition.
So far, everything is in perfect order.
But problems start to appear after a while.
Unlike the driving model, the collision model is no longer very good.
We don&#39;t expect this type of game to calculate complex deformations and collisions, but if you have virtually no idea how your car will behave before virtually any impact on any object, then everything is probably not quite right.
Typically, when overtaking or passing cars in normal traffic, sometimes you only lick each other slightly, but other times in an almost identical situation, your car will end up in wild pirouettes.
Or even straightforward.
Thanks to the system of restarts, it doesn&#39;t matter much, but it will upset you reliably.
Restarts are solved in such a way that if you smash or drive far off the track, the game throws you back to the last clue point on the track.
But there are only five restarts available in each race.
When you run out of them, you have to start the race again from the beginning.
So it&#39;s more of a tool in case something goes wrong than you can rely on them.
But sometimes even restarts don&#39;t help, they will only be solved by the need to memorize a given section of the race.
The big draw of the game is that the same things often happen in the same places.
For example, some corners need to be traversed in a specific way, otherwise you simply cannot fit into them.
Other times, you will always meet &quot;civilian&quot; cars in the same configuration, whether you arrive first, fifth, five seconds earlier or a minute later.
This is especially annoying in situations where you see an opponent passing easily between two oncoming cars in front of you, while when you get there, the cars are already in such a position that you have to go around or brake them.
It doesn&#39;t matter when you reach them, because it is &quot;calculated&quot; so that the situation always occurs just before your nose.
Opponents have another advantage.
During the entire game, you will come across several places where, again regardless of the time, you will always be overtaken by the same opponent in the same place.
It hits the hardest at the end of the game on the long bridge, where you go in the opposite direction.
The opponent must get there in front of you, obviously at any cost.
When he drives in front of you, it makes your overview of oncoming cars worse, so at first you get around a few times.
You can understand the intention to make the game more exciting and adrenaline-fueled, but the design is so obvious that it will reliably disgust you quickly.
And it&#39;s a shame, because despite the simple driving model, playing is fun and sometimes so action-packed that sometimes you literally don&#39;t have time to watch where something is flying.
And it basically doesn&#39;t matter whether the concept with fifty unique tracks, the arrangement of races so that boredom doesn&#39;t stand a chance, or anything else is responsible for that.
An unconventional idea is to change cars during the races.
You have to watch out for petrol stations on the road, because that&#39;s where you can change your car, even though in the vast majority of cases you can do with what you have.
The cars are divided into three categories.
Sports cars are suitable for urban areas, strong American crashes on straight highways and exotic supersports for technical riding, for example on winding mountain roads.
The main story mode goes hand in hand with the challenge mode, which are races in individual locations that you know from the story.
Here you get not only medals, but also experience points for your profile, which is common to challenges and stories.
To gain a higher level of driver, various objects are unlocked: starting with the cars and ending with the background for the profile.
At the same time, it is again connected to the online Autolog function, which, among other things, compares your results with other players and provides other community functions.
One of the other hard-to-understand kicks is the situation from the last race in the story.
With your car you get to the subway tunnel (be it), where you drive in the dark on the tracks (be it).
The numbers on the tachometer flash between 150 and 200 km / h (so be it), and the subway train comes in from behind and scrapes you uncompromisingly.
In the newsroom, we will probably have a discussion for a few more days about whether no one really thought even a bit when creating the game, or whether the authors consider us to be really big idiots.
The technical side of the game is nothing extra, but at least the overall visual impression is in most cases very pleasant and in some cases even great.
It freezes so that in some tense moments the shooting decreases, and in some cases quite tragically.
However, this applies especially to crashes with a larger number of participants, when smooth shooting would no longer be valid for you anyway.
The sound page is fine and the soundtrack is a matter of taste.
In an effort to please the widest possible range of rather younger audiences, a soundtrack from the category &quot;every dog a different village&quot; was created, but it can be assumed that because of listening to music, someone will probably not buy the game just like that.
The overall impression of Need for Speed: The Run is so embarrassing.
If the game avoids completely unnecessary mistakes, then we would not be afraid to say that The Run is the best work of NFS in the last few years.
But this is how the game looks unfinished.
Fun is definitely nice, but be prepared for the mistakes to strike you in the eye with the power of airport searchlights.
