The walls have eyes: How scientists study you on Facebook
Before Anders Behring Breivik became the new face of right-wing extremism in Europe, he was just another young man who presented his anti-immigrant views on the Internet.
On Monday, Braivik, who confessed to the murderous rage in July, which left 77 dead in Norway, attended his first public court hearing.
