This material, slightly edited, forms the basis of Steve Jobs&#39; 68-minute film: The Lost Interview, which is headed to select theaters this Wednesday and Thursday.
For someone who is notorious for his reluctance to provide longer conversations, Jobs is surprisingly enthusiastic here that he can talk about his technological philosophy and business strategies.
