The interview was filmed before the Pixar, iPod or iPhone era, and it has frighteningly prophetic ideas as Jobs assesses what other companies are doing well and badly, offering their own vision of the future in the field of computer technology.
It is one thing to read the posthumous evaluations of Jobs&#39; career, but there is something raw and inspiring about Jobs, whom we see here as an eager dreamer in the heyday of his genius.
He has his own vision of what they might and should look like.
It didn&#39;t take long, and after he expressed his thoughts, he also began to put them into practice.
A quick summary of seven scenes from The Lost Interview, which is definitely worth noting:
How he learned to run a business:
