No one knows why he does what he does, he never thinks about business matters in depth.
That&#39;s what I found out.
Jobs goes on to describe his efforts to simplify accounting at Apple.
He was completely confused by the way costs were recorded - they often started with &quot;standard costs&quot;, he could only guess at the amount. At that moment, he decided to go his own way - he developed an automatic tool that guaranteed that they could determine business costs in a matter of seconds.
How he made the grate for the pope:
