The technological genius that led the company to its unshakable position is now being replaced by people who have no idea about good or bad products - skill and technical knowledge are essential.
That&#39;s exactly what happened at Xerox ...
Xerox could own literally the entire computer industry.
It could have been ten times bigger than it could have been Microsoft in the 1990s ...
Instead of winning, however, they lost to defeat.
How it takes innovation as a form of art:
&quot;There&#39;s still a long way to go between a great idea and a great end product ... and as that great idea develops, it changes and grows.&quot;
During that time, you will learn a lot about him.
