On the contrary, thanks to the invariability of our energy policy, our neighbors will pay an electricity bill 40% higher than what French households pay.
While in a globalized economy, energy costs are a key factor in competitiveness and a guarantee of keeping industry on national territory, French companies enjoy the benefits of the cheapest electricity in Europe.
For this reason, any significant reduction in the share of nuclear energy would lead to a sharp rise in the price of electricity, which would make illusory beautiful statements about the re-industrialization of our country and the defense of purchasing power.
The price that the vast majority of French people refuse to pay, just as they do not oppose this energy in principle, as opinion polls show.
