In Chernobyl, the drama was caused by reactor concepts and inexcusable human error.
In the case of Fukushima, some seem to forget that the accident was the result of two natural disasters of unprecedented scale, which killed tens of thousands of people.
The nuclear industry will learn from this accident in the same way as it did in the previous two.
